    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Saatchi Makes An Appointment</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By STUART ELLIOT</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Steve Rabosky is named chief creative officer at Torrance, Calif, office of Saatchi &amp; Saatchi; succeeds Joe McDonagh, who resigned in January 1999 (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Steve Rabosky, a well-known creative executive, has been named chief creative officer at the Torrance, Calif., office of Saatchi &amp; Saatchi, a position that includes supervision of all creative work for the agency's largest account, Toyota Motor Sales USA.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Steve Rabosky, a well-known creative executive, has been named chief creative officer at the Torrance, Calif., office of Saatchi &amp; Saatchi, a position that includes supervision of all creative work for the agency's largest account, Toyota Motor Sales USA.</p>
        <p>Mr. Rabosky, 46, succeeds Joe McDonagh, who left the agency in January 1999 to become co-president and executive creative director at the Los Angeles office of Ogilvy &amp; Mather Worldwide, part of the WPP Group. Mr. Rabosky had most recently been chief creative officer at the London office of Ammirati Puris Lintas; he left after that agency was merged with Lowe &amp; Partners to form Lowe Lintas &amp; Partners Worldwide, part of the Lowe Group unit of the Interpublic Group of Companies.</p>
        <p>THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
